ivardefs.name: author
ivardefs.desc: The logical author of the message - the person or device that decided the described event should happen. When there is more than one candidate, pick the most proximal to the MessageHeader. Can provide other authors in extensions.

ivardefs.name: definition
ivardefs.desc: Permanent link to the MessageDefinition for this message.

ivardefs.name: destination_
ivardefs.desc: The destination application which the message is intended for.

ivardefs.name: enterer
ivardefs.desc: The person or device that performed the data entry leading to this message. When there is more than one candidate, pick the most proximal to the message. Can provide other enterers in extensions.

ivardefs.name: focus_
ivardefs.desc: The actual data of the message - a reference to the root/focus class of the event.

ivardefs.name: reason
ivardefs.desc: Coded indication of the cause for the event - indicates  a reason for the occurrence of the event that is a focus of this message.

ivardefs.name: response
ivardefs.desc: Information about the message that this message is a response to.  Only present if this message is a response.

ivardefs.name: responsible
ivardefs.desc: The person or organization that accepts overall responsibility for the contents of the message. The implication is that the message event happened under the policies of the responsible party.

ivardefs.name: sender
ivardefs.desc: Identifies the sending system to allow the use of a trust relationship.

ivardefs.name: source
ivardefs.desc: The source application from which this message originated.
